	  <concept id="id1617MD00HIT"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">3.501-2</ph> General.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d118e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d120e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Buying-in may decrease competition or result in poor contract performance. The contracting officer must take appropriate action to ensure buying-in losses are not recovered by the contractor through the pricing of-</p>
					          <ol id="d118e23" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d120e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Change orders; or</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d120e36" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Follow-on contracts subject to cost analysis.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d120e47" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The Government should minimize the opportunity for buying-in by seeking a price commitment covering as much of the entire program concerned as is practical by using-</p>
					          <ol id="d118e53" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d120e57" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Multiyear contracting, with a requirement in the solicitation that a price be submitted only for the total multi-year quantity; or</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d120e66" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Priced options for additional quantities that, together with the firm contract quantity, equal the program requirements (see <xref href="FAR-i1103024.dita#i1103024"
                              base="i1103024"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  17.2</xref>).</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d120e80" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Other safeguards are available to the contracting officer to preclude recovery of buying-in losses (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i>amortization of nonrecurring costs (see <xref href="FAR-i1106593.dita#i1106593"
                        base="i1106593"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.408</xref>, <xref href="FAR-i1106593.dita#i1106593/i1106753"
                        base="i1106753"
                        outputclass="fm:Table"
                        class="- topic/xref ">Table  15-2</xref>, paragraph A, column (2) <ph class="- topic/ph ">under “Formats for Submission of Line Item Summaries”)</ph> and treatment of unreasonable price quotations (see <xref href="FAR-i1106373.dita#i1106373"
                        base="i1106373"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.405</xref>).</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
